The Well-Architected Framework

 
First Pillar - Reliability
 
Reliability is the ability of a system to recover from infrastructure or service disruptions, 
dynamically acquire compute resources to meet demand and mitigate disruptions such as misconfigurations or transient network issues.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
second pillar - Performance Efficiency

It is the ability to use computing resources efficiently to meet system requirements.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Third pillar - Security
The ability to protect information, systems and assets while delivering business value through risk assessments and mitigation strategies.
 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fourth pillar - Cost Optimization
The ability to run systems to deliver business value at the lowest price point. 
It's hard to optimize for cost without compromising other areas. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Final pillar - Operational Excellence
The ability to run and monitor systems to deliver business value and to continually improve
supporting processes and procedures. 
